SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An individual that came into contact with a source of Tuberculosis.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Subject in Contact With Tuberculosis Source

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An individual who is presently or not long ago worked or offered to assist without pay at a temporary housing facility for persons without a stable or permanent residence.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: CURRENT OR RECENT EMPLOYEE OR VOLUNTEER IN HOMELESS SHELTER
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Current or Recent Employee or Volunteer in Homeless Shelter

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An individual who is presently or not long ago worked or offered to assist without pay at an institution where persons are confined for punishment and to protect the public.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: CURRENT OR RECENT EMPLOYEE OR VOLUNTEER IN JAIL OR PRISON
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Current or Recent Employee or Volunteer in Jail or Prison

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An individual who is presently or not long ago worked or offered to assist without pay at a residential health care facility for persons with chronic illness or disability.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: CURRENT OR RECENT EMPLOYEE OR VOLUNTEER IN NURSING HOME
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Current or Recent Employee or Volunteer in Nursing Home

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An individual without a stable or permanent residence within the last 365 days.
An individual that has migrated from a country with a high occurrence of tuberculosis.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: IMMIGRANT FROM HIGH TUBERCULOSIS PREVALENT AREA
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Immigrant From High Tuberculosis Prevalent Area

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The state of being confined to jail or prison.
An individual that resided in a camp for those displaced from their homeland.

An individual that lives at a healthcare facility that provides rehabilitative, restorative, and/or ongoing skilled nursing care to patients or residents in need of assistance with activities of daily living.
An individual who moves from one location to another location within or outside of their homeland for work.
An individual that has fled a country for their own safety which has a high occurrence of tuberculosis.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: REFUGEE FROM HIGH TUBERCULOSIS PREVALENT AREA
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Refugee From High Tuberculosis Prevalent Area

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: Entry into one or more of the 22 countries that have a relatively high prevalence of tuberculosis cases.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Travel To High Burden Tuberculosis Country

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The state of not having a job.
